As per joint report JE/SIG/RRL Attended with EI Engg and found   , Initial status of El system A1 to A6 all are online (working). MLKII
System card file A2 was working healthy in online mode along with MLKII System file B2
in offline (partner)mode. suddenly card file A2 got reset with Error [error]10/12
01:07:42.9 PM Internal Vector error - BUS_ERROR_VEC, return address, [error] 10/12
01:08:13.0 PM Sync Verification error - Mode: 03 Partner, B2 also got Reset with recorded
error [error] 10/12 01:07:42.6 PM Sync Quarantine Transition - Mode = 02 and hence
both card file C2 (A2 & B2 ) Reset simultaneously .As a result, Communication break C2
to other card-file.
Correction Action Taken:
During failure investigation Hitachi engineer examined the card-file's A2 has error Internal
Vector error - BUS_ERROR_VEC, return address: 0009B1AC 040D 0009 B1AC
00C8 for that ECB PCB has been changed and then MLK II-B2 SYNC PCB power supply wiring
& other parameters, and ensure proper intactness of terminal, apart from, also measured
the voltages on respective terminals and observation.
A2 Running system & B2 Hot stand by system working. Now both MLKII System card files
system working normal.
NOTE- Information received by JE/SIG/RRL 13:09 HRS
Attened time 13:11HRS. (13:10 HRS both system & VDU are steady but some route
are lock. 13:25 HRS all Route released are completed.)
System block time 17:20 to 17:35HRS. During block MLK A2 System ECB card changed & all
terminal are tighten. Now both system are working properly(A1 to A6 Online & B1 to B6
Offline).

ADSTE/BYT, SSE/SIG/BYL ALONG WITH JE/SIG/DGS ATTENDED AT AUTO HUT-02 AND FOUND THAT ALL PARAMETERS WERE WITHIN LIMIT. ALL THE AXLE COUNTERS WERE RESET BY ON DUTY STATION STAFF FROM BOTH ENDS AND CLEARED AFTER PASSAGE OF 01 TRAIN IN EACH LINE. LATER, WHILE INVESTIGATION IT WAS FOUND THAT ALL THE AXLE COUNTERS (BOTH MAIN AND STANDBY) FAILED AT SAME TIME AT 00:19 HRS. AT THE SAME TIME, DATA LOGGER EQUIPMENT INSIDE AUTO HUT-2 ALSO GOT RESET. POWER SUPPLY TO DATA LOGGER EQUIPMENT WAS GIVEN FROM EXT-24VDC SUPPLY OF MINI-IPS. ALSO, ERROR LOGS WERE EXTRACTED FROM EC OF MSDAC (FOR BOTH A & B SYSTEMS) AND FOUND THAT ALL DPs FAILED WITH SAME ERROR (FDP_UNIT_FAILED). AS PER GGT-MSDAC MANUAL THIS ERROR IS GENERATED DURING POWER FAILURE IN FDP UNIT. FROM ALL THE ABOVE, THIS IT IS CONCLUDED THAT A FLUCTUATION/INTERRUPTION HAS OCCURRED IN THE POWER SUPPLY OF MINI-IPS WHICH INTERRUPTED ALL THE DC POWER SUPPLIES AND RESULTED IN THIS FAILURE. ISSUE IS BEING TAKEN UP WITH OEM (HBL IPS) FOR THOROUGH INVESTIGATION. IPS DETAILS: MAKE: HBL (MINI-IPS), SR NO: 2K16/644, DOI: 13.04.2025, LAST AMC: 23.09.2025

JE/SIG/GTW Apoorv, SSE/Sig no.-1/BSP Sahu attended and reported that West yard point no.- 158B(TWS point, stroke- 220mm) block for point machine replacement applied for 1 hrs 30 min but SCR/BSP allowed only for 1 hrs from 10:45hrs to 11:45hrs & later point replacement work was completed on 12:25hrs. This point is not required for UP & DN movements. This point operation is required for siding movements. Reason for block exceeded- (1) Misalignment of point machine screw. (2) Adverse site condications including heavy coal accumulation and proximity of a drain line beside the point machine. (3) The old point machine was of CG make, While the newly installed point machine is of podanur make, Which requires modification of the ground connection to the detection slide in accordance with the manufacture's specifications for the new machine. SSE/sig/DGG and JE/sig/DGG attended and found that the transformer module located in the Center IPS room (below 600 meters) was failed due to a fuse blown off (rating: 6 Amps). Although the fuse was replaced, the issue persisted because the 110V AC supply was not extended from the Center to West Goomty.
Upon further analysis to identify the fault, they discovered that the signaling cable 1X24 core carrying the 110V AC supply from the Center to West Goomty via JB, specifically the 1x24 core cable, cores No. 4, 5, and 6 (for BX 110V AC) and cores 17, 18, and 19 (for NX110 AC), cable had low insulation from JB to West Goomty. This cable damage was suspected to have occurred during the work on the fourth line. To resolve the issue, the 110V AC circuit was shifted to a 2-core (70 sq mm) power cable from the Center to West Goomty via the JB, after the failure was rectified permanently.

Up line advance starter signal S-27, down line advance starter S-28 & Joint line auto signal S-18 & DJA344 failed automatically due to 27TSR, 28TSR, 18TSR & DJA344TSR dropped at 03:58hrs. As per joint report SSE/Sig/RJN & Hitachi Engineer attended & found MLKII system card-file "B1" was working healthy in online mode along with MLKII system card-file "A1" in offline (partner) mode. Suddenly card-file "B1" got reset with error log "System timer watch dog time out- Idle loop" at 03:58:21hrs. Simultaneoulsy, the MLKII system card-file "A1" also got reset with recorded error " Sync Qurantine transition- Mode 02" at 03:58:24hrs and hence both the card-files of C1(A1 & B1) reset simultaneously. As a result, communication break between C1 card-file to other card-files. During failure investigation Hitachi Engineer examined the card-files's & Sync PCB's power supply wiring & other paramters, and ensured proper intactness of terminals. Apart from this also measured the voltages on respective terminals and observed normal. A1 running system & B1 hot standby system working. After passing train up line rectified at 04:28hrs, down line rectified at 04:38hrs & joint line rectified at 04:52hrs. Last date of EI system changeover-20.05.25 from A to B. As per datalogger in PMS-SSI 27TSR, 28TSR dropped at 03:58:28hrs & 18TSR, DJA344TSR dropped at 03:58:58hrs later 27TSR picked up at 04:28hrs, 28TSR picked up 04:38hrs, 18TSR picked up at 04:47hrs & DJA344TSR picked up at 04:52hrs.

OFC media failed between BMC and BDKD at 10:05 hrs, resulting in the failure of UFSBI and BPAC systems in the same section. JE/T/CWA and the RCIL team from CWA attended the site and carried out OTDR testing from the BDKD end. The OTDR trace indicated a fiber break/cut at 22.70 km towards BMC (section total optical cable length is 25.307 km). Further team operated joint at two location (Km 1307/8 and KM1308/6-7)and conducted OTDR test, which showed the fiber break at 50 meters towards BMC. Then, 60 meters of OFC was replaced near Km 1308/6-7 to rectify the fault. The link was restored at 18:15 hrs. After restoration, both sides' Dy. SS applied reset, reset accepted at 19:24 hrs. The failure was rectified at 20:05 hrs after the passage of a subsequent train. (Error code- 33 in all CPU at BMC), Joint Inspection with RCIL last date of Testing:-31.03.25, Spare fiber losses:- 7.3dB.

SSE/BTC Sir with staff, traveled by road from BTC to HTT Station to check the failure of the S1 Home Signal. Upon investigation, they found that the 1HR relay was not picking up. A thorough inspection of the 1HR circuit revealed that the 1/C1TSR relay was also not picking up. Further examination of the 1/C1TSR circuit identified that the C1CNRR relay contact no. B5 was not extended supply to the 1/C1TSR circuit because of high resistance in back contact B5-B6 (2 mega ohm). After replacing the C1CNRR relay with a new one, the 1/C1TSR relay and the 1HR relay picked up, and then the failure was rectified at 09:45 Hrs. Relay Make CG Style QN1 Contact 8F/8B Date 10/01 Sr.no-AC50951

SSE/Sig/TMR stabled EI system manually in B system after changing Communication card of B5 system and quarantine A1-A6 system at about 11:05hrs. CPU and Communication cards of A5 were also replaced as per the analysis of the failure.

As per SSE/TMR, OHE mast installation work was in progress near DP 21 of MSADC 96T, and during material shifting, the axle counter may have failed. The datalogger report indicated that A96T MSDAC track circuit bobbed at 13:19 hrs, followed by the failure of B96T at the same time, causing A96 TSR to drop. The failure persisted until train 12261 passed, after which B96TPR, A96 TSR picked up at 14:36 hrs, restoring normal working. Subsequently, SSE/SIG/TMR Verma sir attended the site along with staff at LC Gate No. 525 and 526, where they checked both TPR voltages and A98 HBPR voltage, finding them within range. All parameters are within normal limits, and the circuit was kept under observation. The recorded parameter readings included DA21/UB21-60V DC (59.35/60.11V), 24V DC (21.02/21.99V), FS (42.99/43.96), F1 (3.51/3.52 kHz), F2 (6.42/6.42 kHz), UR1 (3.42/3.40), UR2 (3.28/3.19), UE1 (61.04/70.20), UE2 (63.40/71.45), UL (1.39/1.49), and LDC (28.1.25).

ESM/MUP attended with staff and found that point 43B failed in reverse. The actual cause of the failure was the accumulation of dust of ballast mixed with oil after the block of open BT (14:30 to 15:30 on 10.02.25)  which obstructed the point, the issue was addressed by clearing the obstruction and re-oiling the point. The failure occurred at point 43B, which only failed in reverse, causing a delay. However, this did not affect the main line trains movement because point 43 was set in normal. At 23:52, the SISB train arrived on line number 2, followed by NMG/BSL, which was scheduled to be dispatched from line number 1. Due to the point not being set in reverse, NMG/BSL had to be kept on line number 1. The SISB train departed at 00:07, and SHIVNATH Express passed through line number 2 at 00:14, followed by subsequent trains on the same line.The failure was attended  after the 12950 train passed at 00:37 from line no 1, and the issue was rectified by 00:50hrs and NMG/BSL departed from line no 1 at 00:57hrs. The open BT block time was from , rectification completed at 01:00hrs. LDC - 30.01.25 by ESM/MUP.

As per gate man diary entry number 55 of TMR station during closing of gate the up side boom of LC-532 was stuck and become inoperative because the on duty gate man gives multiple commands of open and close during closing, causing it to stuck than on duty gate man operated gate using crank handle still gate indication not obtained than operated sliding barrier still gate close and lock indication of gate is not obtained. Later S&T staff attended and found that the crank handle key is kept out and not insert back to EKT after crank handle operation by on duty gateman due to which the gate close and lock indication was not obtained. S&T staff inserted the crank handle key in respective EKT and gate close and lock indication obtained and failure rectified at 15:21hrs. After that S&T staff operated gate multiple times no fault found and gate is working properly. It is evident from the findings that the incident was caused solely by the improper operation of the gate by the on-duty gateman, including failing to reinsert the crank handle key into the EKT after manual operation. This operational error directly led to the gate's malfunction and the resulting train detention.

MCM/RIG JAISWAL & JE/JSPL AAKANSHA ATTENDED & REPORTED THAT BOTH OPERATING VDU SYSTEM FAILED SUDDENLY DURING MONTHLY MAINTENANCE BY HRSTS ENGINEER SAIKAT. ON THAT TIME "B- VDU" WAS WORKING ONLINE ACTIVE MODE. THEN HRSTS ENGINEER CLEANED "C DRIVE" OF "VDU- A" BY "DISC CLEAN-UP" PROCEDURE. THEN HE RE-STARTED "VDU- A" AND RE-OPENED "HRSTS PANEL.EXE" FILE IN "VDU- A". AT THAT TIME BOTH VDU "A & B" FAILED SUDDENLY. AS AN IMMEDIATE CORRECTIVE ACTION HRSTS ENGINEER CLOSED "HRSTS PANEL.EXE" FILE FROM "VDU- A" AND APPLIED FORCE COMMAND IN "VDU- B". THEN YARD SIMULATION APPEARED IN "VDU- B" BUT YARD OPERATION THROUGH SIMULATION NOT POSSIBLE DUE TO "GN" & "UN" INDICATIONS WERE FLASHING IN "VDU- B". THEN HRSTS ENGINEER RE-STARTED "VDU- B" & OPENED "HRSTS PANEL.EXE" FILE. AFTER THAT NORMAL TRAIN MOVEMENT STARTED FROM "VDU- B" AT 11:10HRS. LATER DURING WINDOWS LOG CHECKING, IT HAS BEEN NOTICED THAT "DISTRIBUTED COM" ERROR APPEARED  ON "VDU- A" & DUE TO THIS ERROR "APPLICATION SPECIFIC PERMISSION" SETTING DID NOT GRANT LAUNCH PERMISSION TO PROGRAME OF "HRSTS PANEL.EXE" FILE OF "VDU- A" THEN DURING CHECKING OF "VDU- A" SETTING MENU FOUND WINDOWS DEFENDER FIREWALL(PUBLIC PORTION) IS IN "ON" STATE. THEN SWITCHED SAME TO "OFF" & RE-OPENED "HRSTS PANEL.EXE" FILE IN "VDU-A". THEN "VDU-A" STARTED WORKING.

*ASSET FAILURE: JSPL BOTH OPERATING VDU SYSTEM "A & B" FAILED SUDDENLY. *DURATION: 10:55hrs to 11:10hrs. *REP: Movement hampered. *S&T REMARKS: BOTH OPERATING VDU SYSTEM FAILED SUDDENLY DURING MONTHLY MAINTENANCE BY HRSTS ENGINEER SAIKAT.  SWITCHED SAME TO "OFF" & RE-OPENED "HRSTS PANEL.EXE" FILE IN "VDU-A". THEN "VDU-A" STARTED WORKING. _x000d_
